# API Base URL Configuration
# 
# This variable sets the base URL for all API requests to the backend.
# 
# Development (local):
#   - If not set, the app will use window.location.origin (same origin as frontend)
#   - Vite's proxy (configured in vite.config.ts) forwards /api requests to http://localhost:8000
#   - For local development, you typically don't need to set this
# 
# Development (remote backend):
#   - If your backend runs on a different host/port, set this to the backend URL
#   - Example: VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000
#   - Example: VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.example.com
#   - Example: VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://192.168.1.100:8000
# 
# Production:
#   - If not set, the app will use window.location.origin (same origin as frontend)
#   - This works when frontend and backend are served from the same domain
#   - If backend is on a different host/port, set this to the backend URL
#   - Example: VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.production.com
# 
# Examples:
#   - Local development (default): Leave unset or use empty string
#   - Remote backend: VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.example.com
#   - Different port: VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000
#   - With path: VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://example.com/api
#
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=
